Note:
PHP Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the PHP translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    PHP source
      -> php_lexer       (tokenize: namespace/class/function/foreach/match/fn,
                          $variables, "interpolated" strings, => arrays)
      -> php_parser      (build the dict-AST documented at the top of php_parser)
      -> php_semantic    (real two-phase scope/name analysis)
      -> php_to_hir      (lower the dict-AST to the hir.runa dictionary/list HIR)
      -> hir_to_php      (emit HIR back to valid PHP text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse / re-semantic / re-to_hir of the emitted text
      -> structural + CONTENT equality on the key constructs

The PHP HIR node model is hir.runa's dictionary/list literal interchange shared by
php_to_hir (producer) and hir_to_php (consumer): a dictionary is a
HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List (16-byte [key, value] blocks) hangs at
the children slot; a list is a HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL whose elements List hangs at the
children slot; string payloads are HIR string-literal nodes read with
get_string_literal_value. This probe reads HIR fields through exactly that contract
(the decoders below mirror the producer/consumer).

DEPTH: the probe does NOT merely check that nodes exist. It asserts on the
re-parsed HIR2 that the CONTENTS survive: namespace name; class name; >= 6 method
names; a typed parameter with a default; a foreach `as $k => $v` (key var + value
var both present); a match expression's arm count (4); an array's `=>` keys; a
closure's use(...) captures; a double-quoted interpolated string. A translator that
returned an empty members list (members vanish) makes this probe FAIL.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/php/php_lexer.runa" as PhpLexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/php/php_parser.runa" as PhpParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/php/php_to_hir.runa" as PhpFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/php/hir_to_php.runa" as PhpBackend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: hir.runa dict/list literal decoders (mirror the producer/consumer contract)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A PHP HIR dictionary is a HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List hangs at the
children slot. Each entry is a 16-byte block: key (raw string handle) at offset 0,
value (a child HIR node or HIR string literal) at offset 8. This decoder
linear-scans those entries comparing the raw key with string_equals, returning the
stored value. It is the exact lookup hir_to_php's get_dictionary_value performs, so
reading HIR through it proves the produced shape is the consumed shape.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with node
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be proc size from List with entries
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, index
        If entry is not equal to 0:
            Let entry_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 0
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
String fields ("_type", "name", "operator", ...) are stored as HIR string literal
nodes. This helper resolves the key then unwraps the literal to its char* payload
via get_string_literal_value, so the probe can compare tags, names, operators.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get_string" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value_node be proc dict_get with node, key
    If value_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with value_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
A PHP HIR list is a HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL whose backing element List hangs at the
children slot. Returning that List lets the probe iterate members / params / arms /
elements / uses with List.size and List.get_at.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_elements" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the element count of a HIR list node (0 when absent). Used to assert match
arm count, member count, array element count, etc.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc size from List with items
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates the program's first top-level node whose "_type" matches the requested
kind. Used to find the namespace and, within it, the class.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_in_list" takes list_node as Integer, type_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If list_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with list_node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let item_type be proc dict_get_string with item, "_type"
        If item_type is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_type, type_name
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return item
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Counts the number of method members in a class's members list, so the probe can
assert the method count survives round-trip.
@End Reasoning
Process called "count_methods" takes members as Integer returns Integer:
    If members is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with members
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let found be 0
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let item_type be proc dict_get_string with item, "_type"
        If item_type is not equal to 0:
            Let type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_type, "method"
            If type_ok is equal to 1:
                Set found to found plus 1
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return found
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates a method member by name within a class's members list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_method" takes members as Integer, want_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If members is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with members
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let item_type be proc dict_get_string with item, "_type"
        If item_type is not equal to 0:
            Let type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_type, "method"
            If type_ok is equal to 1:
                Let item_name be proc dict_get_string with item, "name"
                If item_name is not equal to 0:
                    Let name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_name, want_name
                    If name_ok is equal to 1:
                        Return item
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Scans a method's body block for the first statement (or return value) whose nested
expression tree contains a node of the requested tag. Bodies are statement lists;
the relevant constructs (match, closure, foreach, array) each appear as the value
of a return / expr_stmt / assignment, so this descends one expression level into
each statement. Bounded by body length, so it always terminates.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_tag_in_method" takes method as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If method is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let body be proc dict_get with method, "body"
    If body is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let inner be proc dict_get with body, "body"
    If inner is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc list_elements with inner
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let stmt be proc get_at from List with items, i
        Let found be proc match_stmt_tag with stmt, tag
        If found is not equal to 0:
            Return found
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Inspects one statement for a tagged expression. A statement of the tag itself
matches; a return/expr_stmt/throw whose value/expr is the tag matches; an
expr_stmt holding an assignment whose value is the tag matches. Returns the tagged
node or 0.
@End Reasoning
Process called "match_stmt_tag" takes stmt as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If stmt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let stmt_type be proc dict_get_string with stmt, "_type"
    If stmt_type is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let direct be proc string_equals from StringCore with stmt_type, tag
    If direct is equal to 1:
        Return stmt
    End If

    Note: return value / print-expr / throw-expr
    Let value be proc dict_get with stmt, "value"
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Let v_ok be proc node_has_tag with value, tag
        If v_ok is not equal to 0:
            Return v_ok
        End If
    End If

    Note: expr_stmt -> expr (which may be an assignment)
    Let expr be proc dict_get with stmt, "expr"
    If expr is not equal to 0:
        Let e_ok be proc node_has_tag with expr, tag
        If e_ok is not equal to 0:
            Return e_ok
        End If
        Let assign_value be proc dict_get with expr, "value"
        If assign_value is not equal to 0:
            Let av_ok be proc node_has_tag with assign_value, tag
            If av_ok is not equal to 0:
                Return av_ok
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the node when its "_type" equals tag, else 0. Single-level tag check.
@End Reasoning
Process called "node_has_tag" takes node as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nt be proc dict_get_string with node, "_type"
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, tag
    If ok is equal to 1:
        Return node
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when an array's elements list contains an array_item whose key is a string
literal whose decoded/raw value equals the target. Used to assert the array's `=>`
keys survive. The key node is a "string" node carrying value/decoded.
@End Reasoning
Process called "array_has_string_key" takes array_node as Integer, want_key as Integer returns Integer:
    If array_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let elements be proc dict_get with array_node, "elements"
    Let items be proc list_elements with elements
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc get_at from List with items, index
        If item is not equal to 0:
            Let key be proc dict_get with item, "key"
            If key is not equal to 0:
                Let decoded be proc dict_get_string with key, "decoded"
                If decoded is not equal to 0:
                    Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with decoded, want_key
                    If matches is equal to 1:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a closure's uses list contains a capture whose name equals the
target. Used to assert the closure's use(...) captures survive.
@End Reasoning
Process called "closure_has_use" takes closure_node as Integer, want_name as Integer returns Integer:
    If closure_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let uses be proc dict_get with closure_node, "uses"
    Let items be proc list_elements with uses
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with items
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let use_node be proc get_at from List with items, index
        Let uname be proc dict_get_string with use_node, "name"
        If uname is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with uname, want_name
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pipeline helper
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Each round of the probe runs the identical front-of-pipeline (lex -> parse ->
semantic -> to_hir). php_to_hir_from_source already runs all of these as a unit;
this wrapper just guards the source so the two runs (original and emitted) are
behaviourally identical and any divergence is attributable to the emitter.
@End Reasoning
Process called "source_to_hir" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    If source is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc php_to_hir_from_source from PhpFrontend with source
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates the program's class node: the program body holds a namespace whose body
holds the class. Returns the class HIR dict or 0.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_class" takes hir_root as Integer returns Integer:
    Let body be proc dict_get with hir_root, "body"
    Let namespace be proc find_in_list with body, "namespace"
    If namespace is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let nbody be proc dict_get with namespace, "body"
    Return proc find_in_list with nbody, "class"
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "PHP translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative program exercising a broad declaration surface:
    - namespace App\Service
    - class Calculator with 6 methods (__construct + 5 named)
    - a typed parameter with a default (int $base = 10)
    - a foreach with `as $k => $v`
    - a match expression of 4 arms
    - an array literal with => keys ("alpha", "beta")
    - a closure capturing via use($factor)
    - a double-quoted interpolated string "Result: $sum"
    :End Note
    Let source be "<?php\nnamespace App {\nclass Calculator {\nprivate int $total = 0;\npublic function __construct(int $base = 10) {\n$this->total = $base;\n}\npublic function add(int $x): int {\n$sum = $this->total + $x;\nreturn $sum;\n}\npublic function describe(int $sum): string {\nreturn \"Result: $sum\";\n}\npublic function tally(array $items): int {\nforeach ($items as $k => $v) {\n$this->total = $this->total + $v;\n}\nreturn $this->total;\n}\npublic function grade(int $score): string {\nreturn match ($score) {\n1, 2 => \"low\",\n3, 4 => \"mid\",\n5 => \"high\",\ndefault => \"none\",\n};\n}\npublic function scaler(int $factor): callable {\nreturn function (int $n) use ($factor): int {\nreturn $n * $factor;\n};\n}\npublic function labels(): array {\nreturn [\"alpha\" => 1, \"beta\" => 2];\n}\n}\n}\n"

    Note: --- Stage 0-2: source -> HIR1 (lex, parse, semantic, lower) ---
    Let tokens be proc php_lex from PhpLexer with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "lexer produced tokens", tokens

    Let parser be proc create_php_parser from PhpParser with tokens
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser created", parser

    Let ast be proc parse_program from PhpParser with parser
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser produced PHP AST", ast

    Let hir1 be proc php_to_hir_from_source from PhpFrontend with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR program", hir1

    Note: Root must be a dict node tagged "php_program" with a body.
    Let prog_type be proc dict_get_string with hir1, "_type"
    Let prog_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with prog_type, "php_program"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "HIR root is a php_program", prog_type_ok, 1

    Let body be proc dict_get with hir1, "body"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "program has a body", body

    Note: --- namespace name survives ---
    Let namespace be proc find_in_list with body, "namespace"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "namespace node present", namespace
    Let ns_name be proc dict_get_string with namespace, "name"
    Let ns_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with ns_name, "App"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "namespace name is 'App'", ns_name_ok, 1

    Note: --- class name + method count survive ---
    Let cls be proc find_class with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "class node present", cls
    Let cls_name be proc dict_get_string with cls, "name"
    Let cls_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with cls_name, "Calculator"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "class name is 'Calculator'", cls_name_ok, 1

    Let members be proc dict_get with cls, "members"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "class has members", members
    Let method_count be proc count_methods with members
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "class has >= 6 methods", method_count, 6

    Let m_construct be proc find_method with members, "__construct"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method '__construct' present", m_construct
    Let m_add be proc find_method with members, "add"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method 'add' present", m_add
    Let m_tally be proc find_method with members, "tally"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method 'tally' present", m_tally
    Let m_grade be proc find_method with members, "grade"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method 'grade' present", m_grade
    Let m_scaler be proc find_method with members, "scaler"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method 'scaler' present", m_scaler
    Let m_labels be proc find_method with members, "labels"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method 'labels' present", m_labels
    Let m_describe be proc find_method with members, "describe"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method 'describe' present", m_describe

    Note: --- typed param + default survive (__construct: int $base = 10) ---
    Let ctor_params be proc dict_get with m_construct, "params"
    Let ctor_param_count be proc list_count with ctor_params
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "ctor has >= 1 param", ctor_param_count, 1
    Let ctor_param_items be proc list_elements with ctor_params
    Let ctor_param0 be proc get_at from List with ctor_param_items, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "ctor param 0 present", ctor_param0
    Let ctor_param_type be proc dict_get_string with ctor_param0, "type"
    Let ctor_param_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor_param_type, "int"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "ctor param 0 type is 'int'", ctor_param_type_ok, 1
    Let ctor_param_default be proc dict_get with ctor_param0, "default"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "ctor param 0 has a default", ctor_param_default

    Note: --- foreach `as $k => $v` survives (tally) ---
    Let foreach_node be proc find_tag_in_method with m_tally, "foreach"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "foreach node present in tally()", foreach_node
    Let foreach_key be proc dict_get with foreach_node, "key_var"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "foreach has a key var ($k)", foreach_key
    Let foreach_value be proc dict_get with foreach_node, "value_var"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "foreach has a value var ($v)", foreach_value

    Note: --- match arm count = 4 survives (grade) ---
    Let match_node be proc find_tag_in_method with m_grade, "match"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "match node present in grade()", match_node
    Let match_arms be proc dict_get with match_node, "arms"
    Let match_arm_count be proc list_count with match_arms
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "match has 4 arms", match_arm_count, 4

    Note: --- array `=>` keys survive (labels) ---
    Let array_node be proc find_tag_in_method with m_labels, "array"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "array node present in labels()", array_node
    Let array_count be proc list_count with array_node
    Let array_elems be proc dict_get with array_node, "elements"
    Let array_elem_count be proc list_count with array_elems
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "array has 2 elements", array_elem_count, 2
    Let has_alpha be proc array_has_string_key with array_node, "alpha"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "array has key 'alpha'", has_alpha, 1
    Let has_beta be proc array_has_string_key with array_node, "beta"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "array has key 'beta'", has_beta, 1

    Note: --- closure use(...) captures survive (scaler) ---
    Let closure_node be proc find_tag_in_method with m_scaler, "closure"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "closure node present in scaler()", closure_node
    Let has_factor be proc closure_has_use with closure_node, "$factor"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "closure captures use($factor)", has_factor, 1

    Note: --- double-quoted interpolated string survives (describe) ---
    Let str_node be proc find_tag_in_method with m_describe, "string"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "interpolated string node present in describe()", str_node
    Let str_interp be proc dict_get_string with str_node, "interpolated"
    Let str_interp_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with str_interp, "1"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "describe string is interpolated", str_interp_ok, 1
    Let str_kind be proc dict_get_string with str_node, "kind"
    Let str_kind_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with str_kind, "double"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "describe string kind is 'double'", str_kind_ok, 1

    Note: --- Stage 3: HIR1 -> PHP text ---
    Let emitted be proc generate_php_from_hir from PhpBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced PHP text", emitted
    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted PHP is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 4: re-run the pipeline on the emitted text -> HIR2 ---
    Let hir2 be proc source_to_hir with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted PHP produced HIR2", hir2

    Let prog2_type be proc dict_get_string with hir2, "_type"
    Let prog2_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with prog2_type, "php_program"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip root is a php_program", prog2_type_ok, 1

    Note: --- Stage 5: CONTENT equality on the key constructs (HIR2) ---

    Note: namespace name survives round-trip
    Let body2 be proc dict_get with hir2, "body"
    Let namespace2 be proc find_in_list with body2, "namespace"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves namespace node", namespace2
    Let ns2_name be proc dict_get_string with namespace2, "name"
    Let ns2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with ns2_name, "App"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves namespace 'App'", ns2_name_ok, 1

    Note: class name + method count survive round-trip
    Let cls2 be proc find_class with hir2
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves class node", cls2
    Let cls2_name be proc dict_get_string with cls2, "name"
    Let cls2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with cls2_name, "Calculator"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves class 'Calculator'", cls2_name_ok, 1

    Let members2 be proc dict_get with cls2, "members"
    Let method2_count be proc count_methods with members2
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves >= 6 methods", method2_count, 6

    Let m2_construct be proc find_method with members2, "__construct"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves '__construct'", m2_construct
    Let m2_grade be proc find_method with members2, "grade"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'grade'", m2_grade
    Let m2_tally be proc find_method with members2, "tally"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'tally'", m2_tally
    Let m2_scaler be proc find_method with members2, "scaler"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'scaler'", m2_scaler
    Let m2_labels be proc find_method with members2, "labels"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'labels'", m2_labels
    Let m2_describe be proc find_method with members2, "describe"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 'describe'", m2_describe

    Note: typed param + default survive round-trip
    Let ctor2_params be proc dict_get with m2_construct, "params"
    Let ctor2_param_items be proc list_elements with ctor2_params
    Let ctor2_param0 be proc get_at from List with ctor2_param_items, 0
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip ctor param 0 present", ctor2_param0
    Let ctor2_param_type be proc dict_get_string with ctor2_param0, "type"
    Let ctor2_param_type_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with ctor2_param_type, "int"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves ctor param type 'int'", ctor2_param_type_ok, 1
    Let ctor2_param_default be proc dict_get with ctor2_param0, "default"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves ctor param default", ctor2_param_default

    Note: foreach `as $k => $v` survives round-trip
    Let foreach2 be proc find_tag_in_method with m2_tally, "foreach"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves foreach node", foreach2
    Let foreach2_key be proc dict_get with foreach2, "key_var"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves foreach key var", foreach2_key
    Let foreach2_value be proc dict_get with foreach2, "value_var"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves foreach value var", foreach2_value

    Note: match arm count survives round-trip
    Let match2 be proc find_tag_in_method with m2_grade, "match"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves match node", match2
    Let match2_arms be proc dict_get with match2, "arms"
    Let match2_arm_count be proc list_count with match2_arms
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 4 match arms", match2_arm_count, 4

    Note: array `=>` keys survive round-trip
    Let array2 be proc find_tag_in_method with m2_labels, "array"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves array node", array2
    Let has_alpha2 be proc array_has_string_key with array2, "alpha"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves array key 'alpha'", has_alpha2, 1
    Let has_beta2 be proc array_has_string_key with array2, "beta"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves array key 'beta'", has_beta2, 1

    Note: closure use(...) captures survive round-trip
    Let closure2 be proc find_tag_in_method with m2_scaler, "closure"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves closure node", closure2
    Let has_factor2 be proc closure_has_use with closure2, "$factor"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves closure use($factor)", has_factor2, 1

    Note: interpolated string survives round-trip
    Let str2 be proc find_tag_in_method with m2_describe, "string"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves interpolated string", str2
    Let str2_interp be proc dict_get_string with str2, "interpolated"
    Let str2_interp_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with str2_interp, "1"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves interpolation flag", str2_interp_ok, 1
    Let str2_kind be proc dict_get_string with str2, "kind"
    Let str2_kind_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with str2_kind, "double"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves double-quote kind", str2_kind_ok, 1

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
